{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016hoMMURFQ9xbGEw2hHnkTQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the replica set looks healthy right now! The precondition injected a fault using `rs.reconfig` with a bad host for member 1. But the current status shows member 1 as SECONDARY and healthy. \n\nWait, actually the precondition log shows that the `mongo_seed_fixture` probe succeeded (meaning it already found ≥3 docs). Also the precondition log shows it WAS run on an inherited cluster - the first `mongo_env_ready` probe found the StatefulSet already running so it skipped the destructive apply. So the inherited cluster (from the previous deploy stage) already had a healthy replica set.\n \nSo the fault injection with the bad host configuration was actually skipped entirely because the StatefulSet was already running when the probe checked it. The `mongo_seed_fixture` then added the documents, but since the apply step never ran, the fault injection never happened. Now I need to look at what the oracle is actually validating to understand what went wrong.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":513,"cache_read_input_tokens":34616,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":513},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0fd6bd49-2f16-41ca-ade7-00246ade79e6","uuid":"ab647407-b87d-42d7-9d71-2907d4b2cc77","request_id":"req_011CcgG3Ak3p2QF7vyRTawB3"}
